      "shadow": "When the drive for Ambition and Structure becomes excessive or blocked, the shadow emerges as **rigidity, emotional coldness, and cynical pessimism**. Ambition can warp into a relentless, status-obsessed climb, using people as stepping stones. Structure becomes a prison of control, manifesting as workaholism, joyless discipline, and fear of spontaneity. Blocked energy often leads to **chronic depression** (Saturn's melancholy), a sense of being burdened by duty, and resentment towards perceived underachievers. The shadow critic is internalized, leading to harsh self-judgment and an inability to celebrate small wins, perpetually postponing happiness until an ever-receding future goal is achieved.",
